<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Spammed-mail-folder.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Spammed-mail-folder.png/300px-Spammed-mail-folder.png" width="300" height="166" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Spammed-mail-folder.png/450px-Spammed-mail-folder.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Spammed-mail-folder.png/600px-Spammed-mail-folder.png 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Spammed-mail-folder.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
An email box folder littered with spam messages</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png/300px-Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png" width="300" height="86" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png/450px-Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png/600px-Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Viagra_Spam_Mail_2011.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A typical spam mail, allegedly for a sex drug (2011)</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Spam</b> is the use of <a href="Email" title="Email">electronic messaging</a> systems to send unsolicited bulk messages, especially advertising, indiscriminately. While the most widely recognized form of spam is <a href="E-mail_spam" title="E-mail spam" class="mw-redirect">e-mail spam</a>, the term is applied to similar abuses in other media.</p>
<p>Spamming remains economically viable because advertisers have no operating costs beyond the management of their mailing lists, and it is difficult to hold senders accountable for their mass mailings. Because the <a href="Barriers_to_entry" title="Barriers to entry">barrier to entry</a> is so low, spammers are numerous, and the volume of unsolicited mail has become very high. In the year 2011, the estimated figure for spam messages is around seven trillion. The costs, such as lost productivity and fraud, are borne by the public and by <a href="Internet_service_provider" title="Internet service provider">Internet service providers</a>, which have been forced to add extra capacity to cope with the deluge. Spamming has been the subject of legislation in many jurisdictions.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>A person who creates electronic spam is called a <i>spammer</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-Gyongyi_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Gyongyi-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
